- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.

a.title: ― DataSet: Organized collection of data based on keys.
a.xlink:title: ― DataSet: Organized collection of data based on keys.

a.title: ― InstanceKey: Single-valued key representation produced from the merge of the representations of all key members and a descriptor.
a.xlink:title: ― InstanceKey: Single-valued key representation produced from the merge of the representations of all key members and a descriptor.

a.title: ― InstanceVariable: Use of a represented variable within a data set.
a.xlink:title: ― InstanceVariable: Use of a represented variable within a data set.

a.title: ― Key: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― Key: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dataset.

a.title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.

a.title: ― WideKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a wide dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― WideKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a wide dataset.

a.title: ― DataPointRelationship: Relations used by the data point relation structure of a logical record to describe specific source-target data points and their relationship.
a.xlink:title: ― DataPointRelationship: Relations used by the data point relation structure of a logical record to describe specific source-target data points and their relationship.

a.title: ― InstanceValue: Single data instance corresponding to a concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived.
a.xlink:title: ― InstanceValue: Single data instance corresponding to a concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived.

a.title: ― ValueMapping: Physical characteristics for the value of an instance variable stored in a data point as part of a physical segment layout.
a.xlink:title: ― ValueMapping: Physical characteristics for the value of an instance variable stored in a data point as part of a physical segment layout.

a.title: ― LongKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a long dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― LongKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a long dataset.

a.title: ― DataPointPosition: Indexed location of the associated member within the associated list.
a.xlink:title: ― DataPointPosition: Indexed location of the associated member within the associated list.

a.title: ― DimensionalKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dimensional dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― DimensionalKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dimensional dataset.

a.title: ― DataStructureComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a data structure.
a.xlink:title: ― DataStructureComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a data structure.

a.title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).
a.xlink:title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).

a.title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.
a.xlink:title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― isDescribedBy: The instance variable delimits the values which can populate a data point. Data point is described by one instance variable.
